        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-09-05 23:06:42.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nI added the settings file, but the test still failed. It actually looks like an issue in the job, because it's failing due to a missing mvn goal. I checked the two other places I could find gerrit-tox-sonar in ONAP, and they're failing too:\nhttps://jenkins.onap.org/view/vnfsdk/job/vnfsdk-dovetail-integration-tox-sonar/\nhttps://jenkins.onap.org/view/vnfsdk/job/vnfsdk-pkgtools-tox-sonar/",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "47bcde4b3b680bb7d5a96c0407d1e7d3dccc3a42",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 681,
          "name": "Chris Lott",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "cl778h@att.com",
          "username": "cl778h"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-09-05 23:47:32.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThanks Eric for the analysis -- do you know what mvn goal is missing, or what the problem is?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "5cee03124ff76c16e15764d7d8850d73327be3fe",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 681,
          "name": "Chris Lott",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "cl778h@att.com",
          "username": "cl778h"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-09-06 01:34:50.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThere seem to be multiple problems here.\n\nThe job is malformed because the first mvn goal is missing, I submitted a patch for that: https://gerrit.linuxfoundation.org/infra/c/releng/global-jjb/+/61612\n\nBut before that is attempted, the tox run fails with an install error.  I have asked Tommy for help.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "5a7d36c457db4104131581c805f76645e43a7d3c",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 681,
          "name": "Chris Lott",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "cl778h@att.com",
          "username": "cl778h"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-09-06 01:37:45.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAnyhow I still think this minor change is zero risk and should be merged.  This build node has a pyenv area with Python 3.7.0 inside it.  The old build node lacks Python 3.7 in its pyenv area.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
